Source: libvirt
Section: devel
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Guido Guenther <agx@sigxcpu.org>
Build-Depends: cdbs (>= 0.4.43), debhelper (>= 5.0.38), libxml2-dev, libncurses5-dev, libreadline5-dev, zlib1g-dev, libgnutls-dev, python-all-dev (>= 2.3.5-11), python-central (>= 0.5.6), quilt
XS-Python-Version: current
Standards-Version: 3.7.2
 Libvirt is a C toolkit to interract with the virtualization capabilities
 of recent versions of Linux (and other OSes). The library aims at providing
 a long term stable C API for different virtualization mechanisms. It currently
 supports QEMU and KVM.

Package: libvirt-bin
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Enhances: qemu, kvm
Description: the programs for the libvirt library
 Libvirt is a C toolkit to interract with the virtualization capabilities
 of recent versions of Linux (and other OSes). The library aims at providing
 a long term stable C API for different virtualization mechanisms. It currently
 supports QEMU and KVM.
 .
 This package contains the supporting binaries to use with libvirt

